Spray 8x4-inch Belgian waffle iron with nonstick cooking spray.** Heat waffle iron. In large bowl, combine quick bread mix, contents of packet from mix, cranberries and oats; mix well. Add buttermilk and eggs; stir 50 to 75 strokes with spoon until mix is moistened. For each waffle, spoon about 1/2 cup batter into hot waffle iron; spread slightly. Cook 2 to 4 minutes or until steaming stops and waffle is golden brown. Top each serving with 1 tablespoon cream cheese. Garnish each serving with 1 teaspoon marmalade.